sounding

Source: R/sounding.R
sounding.Rd

Function calculates presently over 130 atmospheric thermal- and kinematic indices (e.g. CAPE, CIN, Lapse Rates, EHI, STP, SCP, etc...) related mostly to severe weather phenomena (Thunderstorms, Large Hail, Tornadoes, etc...)

sounding(
  pressure,
  altitude,
  temp,
  dpt,
  wd,
  ws,
  export_profile = 0,
  accuracy = 1
)

Arguments

pressure

pressure [hPa]
altitude

altitude [metres]
temp

air temperature [degree Celsius]
dpt

dew point temperature [degree Celsius]
wd

wind direction [degrees]
ws

wind speed [knots or m/s - TODO/TODISCUSS]
export_profile

whether to export interpolated levels for drawing on Skew-T diagram. Binary [0 - default, no extra data for drawing exported, 1 - extracting data to be used ]

Details

Wrapper for a generic sounding function. Please consider using a slightly faster sounding_default() for large databases (i.e. at least over 1,000,000 soundings).

Examples

pressure <- c(1000, 855, 700, 500, 300, 100, 10)
altitude <- c(0, 1500, 2500, 6000, 8500, 12000, 25000)
temp <- c(25, 10, 0, -15, -30, -50, -92)
dpt <- c(20, 5, -5, -30, -55, -80, -99)
wd <- c(0, 90, 135, 180, 270, 350, 0)
ws <- c(5, 10, 20, 30, 40, 5, 0)
options(scipen = 999) # change formatting
sounding(pressure, altitude, temp, dpt, wd, ws)
